action.message:
## Summary

The issue was that `CONFIG RESETSTAT` only reset cluster slot statistics but did not reset the cluster bus message counters (`stats_bus_messages_sent` and `stats_bus_messages_received`).

### Change Made

**File:** `src/cluster.c` — `resetClusterStats()` function

Added two `memset()` calls to zero out both bus message counter arrays in addition to the existing `clusterSlotStatResetAll()` call:

```c
void resetClusterStats(void) {
    if (!server.cluster_enabled) return;

    clusterSlotStatResetAll();
    memset(server.cluster->stats_bus_messages_sent, 0, sizeof(server.cluster->stats_bus_messages_sent));
    memset(server.cluster->stats_bus_messages_received, 0, sizeof(server.cluster->stats_bus_messages_received));
}
```

This follows the same pattern used in the cluster initialization code in `cluster_legacy.c:1260-1263` and ensures that `CONFIG RESETSTAT` properly resets all cluster statistics, including the bus message send/receive counters.

